  "response": "Before receiving revelations, Muhammad, like many members of his tribe, the Quraysh, participated in the traditional polytheistic practices of the region. They worshipped a variety of gods and idols, typical of the pre-Islamic Arabian religious landscape. These included deities like Hubal, Al-Lat, Al-Uzza, and Manat. However, Islamic tradition holds that Muhammad himself was monotheistic and had a contemplative nature, seeking spiritual truth even before his prophethood.",
